The paper deals with differentially private algorithms for answering statistical queries on sensitive databases, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of database systems (cs.DB) and privacy and security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a new algorithm that optimizes error for high-dimensional datasets, which involves techniques from machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the use of matrix representations and efficient search algorithms, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT).
